A fifteen-sided figure is drawn on a $1 \text{ cm}\times 1 \text{ cm}$ graph paper. The figure is composed of several smaller squares and right-angled triangles. What is the area of the figure in $\text{cm}^2$?
{{DGM:db175324cedabf25}}
$\textbf{(A)}\ 9 \qquad \textbf{(B)}\ 10 \qquad \textbf{(C)}\ 11 \qquad \textbf{(D)}\ 12 \qquad \textbf{(E)}\ 14$
